.TH DOUBLETAKE 1 "May 2026" "doubletake" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
doubletake \- AirPlay 2 screen mirroring sender for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B doubletake
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B doubletake
is an AirPlay 2 screen mirroring sender that streams your Linux desktop to an Apple TV
using the AirPlay 2 mirroring protocol. It supports both Wayland (PipeWire/xdg-desktop-portal)
and X11 screen capture with hardware-accelerated H.264 encoding.
.SH FEATURES
.IP \(bu 2
Full AirPlay 2 mirroring protocol (RTSP/HTTP + encrypted video stream)
.IP \(bu 2
FairPlay SAP authentication
.IP \(bu 2
SRP-6a pairing with PIN and persistent credential storage
.IP \(bu 2
Hardware-accelerated H.264 encoding (NVENC, VA-API) with software fallback
.IP \(bu 2
ChaCha20-Poly1305 stream encryption
.IP \(bu 2
mDNS device discovery
.IP \(bu 2
Daemon mode with multi-target streaming control via
.B doubletake-ctl
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-target \fIIP\fR
Connect to a specific Apple TV by IP address (skips mDNS discovery)
.TP
.B \-port \fIPORT\fR
AirPlay port (default: 7000)
.TP
.B \-pin \fIPIN\fR
4-digit PIN for pairing
.TP
.B \-pair
Force new pairing even if credentials exist
.TP
.B \-cred-backend \fIBACKEND\fR
Credential storage backend: \fBfile\fR or \fBkeyring\fR (default: file)
.TP
.B \-creds \fIPATH\fR
Path to credentials file (default: ~/.config/doubletake/credentials.json)
.TP
.B \-width \fIWIDTH\fR
Stream width in pixels (default: 1920)
.TP
.B \-height \fIHEIGHT\fR
Stream height in pixels (default: 1080)
.TP
.B \-fps \fIFPS\fR
Frames per second (default: 30)
.TP
.B \-bitrate \fIKBPS\fR
Target bitrate in kbps (0 = auto, default: 0)
.TP
.B \-target-latency-ms \fIMS\fR
Target playout latency in milliseconds (default: 100)
.TP
.B \-no-audio
Disable audio for video-only mirroring
.TP
.B \-hwaccel \fIMETHOD\fR
Hardware acceleration method: \fBnvenc\fR (NVIDIA) or \fBvaapi\fR (Intel/AMD)
.TP
.B \-debug
Enable verbose protocol logging
.TP
.B \-daemonize
Run in daemon mode for multi-target control via
.B doubletake-ctl
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Discover and connect to any Apple TV on the network:
.B doubletake
.TP
Connect to a specific Apple TV:
.B doubletake \-target 192.168.1.77
.TP
Pair with a PIN (saves credentials for reuse):
.B doubletake \-target 192.168.1.77 \-pair \-pin 1234
.TP
Stream with custom resolution and bitrate:
.B doubletake \-target 192.168.1.77 \-width 1280 \-height 720 \-fps 30 \-bitrate 4500
.TP
Force lower bitrate on weak Wi-Fi:
.B doubletake \-target 192.168.1.77 \-bitrate 3000
.TP
Use hardware acceleration (NVIDIA):
.B doubletake \-target 192.168.1.77 \-hwaccel nvenc
.TP
Run in daemon mode:
.B doubletake \-daemonize
.TP
Debug mode with verbose logging:
.B doubletake \-target 192.168.1.77 \-debug
.SH DAEMON MODE
When run with \fB\-daemonize\fR, doubletake runs as a background service that can control
multiple simultaneous connections. Use
.B doubletake-ctl
to manage the daemon.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.IP \(bu 2
Go 1.23 or later
.IP \(bu 2
GStreamer 1.0 (with plugins-base, plugins-good, plugins-bad, plugins-ugly, libav)
.IP \(bu 2
PipeWire (Wayland) or X11 for screen capture
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/doubletake/credentials.json
Default location for saved AirPlay credentials
.SH SEE ALSO
.B doubletake-ctl(1)
